File: The police are facing tricky questions, after a spike in the number of Cash-in-Transit heists. JOHANNESBURG - Cash-in-transit robbery season appears to be in full swing in Gauteng. Another dramatic heist happened in Evaton in the Emfuleni region on Monday. READ: Explosive CIT robberies increasing again According to eyewitnesses, a Fidelity van was chased by two vehicles and bombed on Adams Road. The unknown assailants opened fire on the guards and managed to get away with an undisclosed amount of money. No one was injured during the heist.